# 🛡️ Empirical Project: SSH Security Weakness Study

## 📌 Introduction

The purpose of this project was to perform an empirical analysis of SSH security by simulating brute-force and dictionary attacks against an SSH service running inside Docker.

The project focused on understanding how password strength and defensive behavior affect resistance against automated attacks. Different SSH user configurations were tested using Hydra, while Nmap was used for reconnaissance and service identification.

The experiment was performed only in a controlled local Docker environment.

---

# 🧪 Methodology

## Environment Setup

The SSH server was deployed using Docker Compose.

### Start the environment

```bash
docker compose up -d
```

### Connect to the SSH server

```bash
ssh student@localhost -p 2222
```

Default credentials:

* Username: `student`
* Password: `password123`

---

## Additional Test Users

Additional users with different password strengths were created for the experiment.

