# ⚔️ Brute-Force Experiments

## Weak Password Test

### Command

```bash
time hydra -l weakuser -P passwords.txt ssh://localhost:2222
```

### Result

Hydra successfully discovered the password:

```text
login: weakuser
password: 123456
```

### Time

```text
0.829s
```

### Analysis

The weak password was cracked almost instantly because it existed in the attacker dictionary. This demonstrates how dangerous predictable passwords are against automated attacks.

---

## Medium Password Test

### Command

```bash
time hydra -l mediumuser -P passwords.txt ssh://localhost:2222
```

### Result

```text
0 valid password found
```

### Time

```text
0.693s
```

### Analysis

The attack failed because the password was not included in the provided dictionary file. This demonstrates that dictionary attacks heavily depend on reused and predictable passwords.

---

## Strong Password Test

### Command

```bash
time hydra -t 4 -l stronguser -P passwords.txt ssh://localhost:2222
```

### Result

```text
0 valid password found
```

### Time

```text
32.707s
```

### Analysis

The strong password resisted the attack successfully. The attack also required significantly more time because the number of parallel Hydra tasks was reduced to maintain stable SSH connections.

